    "The European Commission (2014), refer to it as an important approach to achieving sustainable economic and environmental development.",
    "According to Blomsma and Brennan (2017) and Naustdalslid (2017), the current economic model, which is based on a linear resource flow, is no longer viable (Wackernagel and Beyers, 2019).",
